From: trim21 <trim21@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] lua: define LUA_OK for Lua 5.1 and LuaJIT

LUA_OK was introduced in Lua 5.2. Define it as 0 for compatibility
with Lua 5.1 and LuaJIT (which is based on Lua 5.1).

---
 rtorrent/src/rpc/lua.cc | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/rtorrent/src/rpc/lua.cc b/rtorrent/src/rpc/lua.cc
--- a/rtorrent/src/rpc/lua.cc
+++ b/rtorrent/src/rpc/lua.cc
@@ -11,3 +11,7 @@
 #ifdef HAVE_LUA
 #include <lua.hpp>
+#ifndef LUA_OK
+#define LUA_OK 0
+#endif
 #endif
